  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Speed is the scalar quantity defined as the total distance covered per
    unit time. Simply put, if there is motion, there is speed. Speed does not, and
    cannot, have a negative value. Sometimes, it is interchanged with velocity.


    Velocity
    is the measured speed measured between two

    (2) specified points. It is the
    measured speed in a certain distance at any given instance in time. However,
    unlike speed, velocity is a vector quantity and requires direction. Negative
    velocity values indicate that the objects are moving in the opposite direction.

'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
