  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "\u2022 The crest is the highest point of the transverse wave, while its
    lowest point is called the trough (pronounced as trof). Together, both the crest
    and trough form the wave\u2019s amplitude.\n\n\u2022 A wave\u2019s wavelength
    is the distance between two (2) crests or troughs. \n\n\u2022 A wave\u2019s frequency
    is the number of waves per measured time. Frequency is measured by counting the
    number of complete cycles of a wave within a second, with a complete cycle comprising
    of a fall and rise of the wave."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -4890204404628985631, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
