  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Applying a force over a certain distance is the simplest definition of
    work. Mechanical work (usually shortened as work), as defined in Mechanics, is
    an action of a force, moving in a certain direction, to an object. Meaning, work
    is achieved if the object is moving alongside the direction the force is directed
    at, or the object is moving at a component of the force\u2019s direction. The
    unit of work is Joules (J), named from James Prescott Joule (English physicist).
    \nFormula: W = Fx where F = force and x = fixed distance.\n\nUnfortunately, work
    is not applicable if: \n1. the object is not moving; and\n2. the force being
    applied on the object is perpendicular to the object\u2019s motion\r\n\nSo remember,
    in order to do work:\r\n1. the force and the direction of the resulting, or existing,
    motion is the same; or\r\n2. a component direction of a force acting on the object
    is moving in the same direction as the object\u2019s\r\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -4890204404628985631, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_fontSharedMaterials: []
  m_fontMaterial: {fileID: 0}
