  m_text: "Pressure (P) is a measure of how much force is applied over a given area.
    It is the magnitude of the force on a surface per unit area. The force is perpendicular
    to the surface area. It can be written as \nP = F/A where F = force and A = area."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
