--- !u!114 &2048021905
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 2048021903}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Elastic collision is defined as a type of collision where the concerned
    bodies conserve both energy and momentum upon contact with each other. The best
    way to describe this type of collision is a ball bouncing off the floor. Sure,
    the ball will bounce upon hitting the ground, and it will conserve momentum and
    energy. But each bounce will conserve less and less energy due to the force being
    weaker with each succeeding bounce, until it stop altogether.\n\nThis kind of
    elastic collision is called a contact collision, and is not a perfect collision.
    \n\nThe other type, which is noncontact collision, is almost perfect. The noncontact
    collision is a kind of elastic collision where the objects interact with each
    other, even without direct contact. A perfect example would be a planet slinging
    a space shuttle in another direction.\n\r\nThe two setups of elastic collision.
    The setups, in truth, uses both the scenarios and cases to create one of the
    two outcomes based on its build.\n\nHead-on collision is the type of elastic
    collision where the projectile is moving directly along a straight line. The
    target, upon colliding with the projectile, will then move in the direction the
    projectile is moving at.\n\nThe non-head-on collision is the type of collision
    where the projectile hits the target at a certain angle, in which the resulting
    angle after impact is dependent on the masses of the given objects in collision.
    \r\n\n"
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
