      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Before, our Position is denoted by d, and this is usually associated with
    linear motion. But, it is also applicable to circles, and even rotational motion.
    Here, it denotes the orientation of a rotating object in free space. It also
    represents the direction of the displacement vector drawn from the origin (or
    axis) to the location of the revolving object. Unit is in radians (rads). One
    full rotation is 360\xB0 in degrees or 2\u03C0 rads in radians. Formula: \u03B8
    = d / r where d = distance and r = radius."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -4890204404628985631, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
